post_text:
Good Evening GSD Families,

As a reminder, our food distribution will continue as scheduled on Tuesdays and Fridays from 1-3 at the SMS/CHS bus loop.

Gleaners is also offering free food distribution for families. Please see below.

Gleaners
Free Food Distribution
Households with Children in the Woodhaven, Brownstown & Gibraltar School Districts

Monday, April 27, 2020
1:00 PM to 4:00 PM

Civic Center Park
23101 Hall Road, Woodhaven MI 48183

Helping Our Community during Urgent Times of Need. Households with children who are in need of food are encouraged to attend our upcoming drive-thru food distribution sponsored by Gleaners Community Food Bank.

Stay in your vehicle to limit exposure. Please arrive with an empty trunk. Groceries will be placed into your trunk. Together with Gleaners Community Food Bank, we are taking all necessary precautions to distribute food safely.

Gleaners is an equal opportunity provider.
If you need directions to the site, please contact the Woodhaven Community Center at (734) 675-4926.

post_text:
Dear GSD Community-

As you most likely know, Governor Whitmer has signed an executive order that suspends face-to-face K-12 schools for the remainder of the school year. We wanted to keep you assured that our district has been actively planning for this possibility and we are hopeful to launch an enhanced remote learning plan shortly after the scheduled spring break. In the meantime, we encourage your children to continue to utilize the resources that teachers have been sending, up until this point. Watch for additional communication to come via email.
Stay healthy and stay safe!

Sincerely,
Amy Conway
Superintendent
text:
Dear GSD Community-

As you most likely know, Governor Whitmer has signed an executive order that suspends face-to-face K-12 schools for the remainder of the school year. We wanted to keep you assured that our district has been actively planning for this possibility and we are hopeful to launch an enhanced remote learning plan shortly after the scheduled spring break. In the meantime, we encourage your children to continue to utilize the resources that teachers have been sending, up until this point. Watch for additional communication to come via email.
Stay healthy and stay safe!

Sincerely,
Amy Conway
Superintendent

post_text: Amazing weekend for the CHS Robotics team. The Terror Bytes finished the qualification rounds ranked 9th out of 41 teams. The team then went on to be the first pick of the 5th alliance. They made it to the semi-finals before falling to the eventual champion. During the awards ceremony, Team 6528 won the Quality Award for consistency and execution. This weekend held many firsts for this program that is on the rise.

post_text:
Dear Gibraltar Families,

Unfortunately, someone decided to take my tweet from yesterday and alter it. School is scheduled to be on tomorrow (1/29). When school is cancelled, an edulink email and robo call will be sent out to families and it will be placed on the local television stations. I also post on the district Facebook page and my official twitter account (@superGSD).

Posting on social media is a helpful way to communicate, but there are risks involved. I am very disappointed that someone decided to make this bad decision to cause confusion among our Gibraltar families.

Additionally, please be advised that the windchills projected for Wednesday and Thursday mornings are going to be extremely cold. I will be monitoring these conditions and will be notifying families through the edulink and robo call system if we have to cancel school.

Thank you for your understanding and patience,

Amy Conway

Good Morning GSD Families-

We have been made aware that some families did not receive a phone notification of this morning's school cancellation. Both a call and email were entered and submitted shortly after 5:00AM, to be delivered to all primary contacts of students in the district. We are currently investigating the situation and hope to have it resolved very soon.

This is a timely opportunity for parents to log in to Mi-Star Parent Portal to ensure your phone number and email is up to date. If you need assistance accessing Parent Portal, you can contact the main office at your child's school.

Thank you for your patience and understanding. Please do not hesitate to contact the office of your child's school with any questions.

Good afternoon,

Carlson High School and Shumate Middle School are currently experiencing a power outage, Monday, November 12, 2018. DTE has been dispatched to the school, but we have not received an update regarding restoration. In the meantime, school will continue to run as usual with students released at regular release time. Lunches will continue to run this afternoon with food available for all students.

We recognize that you may wish to pick your child up or have him/her drive home. At Shumate, you will need to come to the office as the phones are currently not working. The phones are working at Carlson if you are calling to give permission for a student to leave or arrange for pick up.

If you wish to take your child out, these class periods will not count towards their overall absence totals.

Thank you,

Jessica Shultz
Principal
Carlson High School

Eric Cassie

Shumate Middle School

post_text: START TIME UPDATE! Parent feedback has been heard regarding the ability to make doctor appointments, sports/activities practices, and other after-school events due to the later ending time of most of our buildings. With that in mind, we have been able to make the following adjustments in start times in most of our buildings for the 18-19 school year. The middle school start and end times have moved up 8 minutes, and all four elementary schools have been moved up to start 10 minutes earlier than last year. We hope this small change will help families with their after-school activities.
